node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

Jumping into the weekend like @faayeded via @johnnybbooyy. 💦 Are your weekend plans as thrilling as this or more on the relaxing side? 🤔

Located in sunny California, Lake Tahoe holds plenty of gems in store for adventure seekers, one of its most daring ones being this rope swing with a roughly 90-foot drop down to the water. As always, it's important to practice extreme caution and training for stunts like this. 🔥

🏃‍♂️ @faayeded
📽 @johnnybbooyy 
📍 Lake Tahoe, California, USA

node.text:
Playful moments via @marysmark. 💦 The killer whale, otherwise known as an orca, inhabit all oceans of the world. While they are most abundant in colder waters like Alaska, Antarctica, and Norway, they are also spotted in tropical and subtropical waters such as in Hawaii, Australia, and the Bahamas.

These powerful whales can range from around 25 to 30 feet in length, often spouting every few seconds while swimming and cruising at the surface, as shown in these creatively merged photos. 🐳

Have you ever spotted an orca in the wild? 🖤

📸 @marysmark
📍  Planet Earth

Epic sunset sessions with @oli_czudny and @yungcoffe in Tenerife, the largest island of the seven Canary Islands which is known for having countless adventures in store. 🛹🔥

Best overhead seats in Dubai with @michutravel. 😍 If you're exploring this cosmopolitan city and looking for a unique experience, take flight in this two-seat gyrocopter that delivers an unparalleled escapade at 1,500 feet high. 🚁

The flight route will take you along the Dubai Marina coastline and past some of the city's most iconic attractions, such as the Dubai Eye (the world’s largest Ferris wheel), Palm Jumeirah, Atlantis Hotel, World Islands, and the spectacular Burj Al Arab. 🇦🇪

Would you hop on this incredible private flight? 

📽 @michutravel
📍 @skyhubdubai, Dubai
🎶 Freedom - Kygo, Zak Abel

Take a moment to immerse in @wanderingbackpack’s glorious lakeside view. It’s truly moments like this that make life beautiful and more meaningful. ✨

From relaxing sunsets and underwater adventures to fun road trips, what do you live for? 🙌🏼

📽 @wanderingbackpack
📍 Montana, USA

Electric blue magic via @louiscole. 💙 Over the years, bioluminescence has been spotted on the California coast in places like Venice Beach. 🌊

Bioluminescence is a chemical reaction that produces light energy within a body of an organism, such as marine algae. This incredible glowing algae can appear during different seasons in Southern California, but has usually been observed in the months of spring in the last few years.

Have you seen bioluminescence in the flesh? 🤩

📽 @louiscole
📍 Venice Beach, California, USA

Mesmerized by @josemostajo's stunning footage of this refreshing waterfall. 😍 Known for its beautiful and unspoiled natural landscapes, Iceland never fails to impress with pristine sights like this. 🇮🇸

With a drop of 60 meters, Seljalandsfoss is a widely popular and breathtakingly stunning waterfall on the south coast of Iceland. There's a path behind the waterfall you can walk on, but make sure to bring a raincoat to avoid getting extremely wet from all the drizzle. 💦

What's the most breathtaking waterfall you've witnessed? ✨

📽 @josemostajo
📍 Seljalandsfoss, Iceland
🎶 Benson - Tides
